MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: SITE IS LOCATED APPROXIMATELY 100 YARDS DOWNSTREAM OF THE M22 BRIDGE AND DIRECTLY BELOW THE CANOE LANDING. THE RIVER AT THIS POINT IS RELATIVELY WIDE AND SHALLOW. MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Back Bay is part of the Bay Mills Whitefish Bay Reserve.  This site is sampled near the area seeded for wild rice.
Back Bay is part of the Bay Mills Whitefish Bay Reserve.  This site is sampled in the deepest part of the bay.
Back Bay is part of the Bay Mills Whitefish Bay Reserve.  This site is sampled at the inlet of a 5th order stream that drains agricultural lands.
The Community College Pond is surrounded by steep sides on the north, west, and south sides.  The east side is a swamp that leads to the beach of the St. Mary's River.
Club Creek Above is a 2nd order stream and is sampled above the Wild Bluff Golf Course.
Club Creek Below is a 2nd order stream and is sampled below the Wild Bluff Golf Course.
Deep Creek is a first order stream and is a stained creek that originates in the Wetland Preserve.  There are no houses near this creek.
Long Marsh is not part of the Bay Mills Wetland Preserve.  The wetland is an important cranberry and blueberry collection area.
The Little Waishkey Above is a 2nd order stream that is sampled above an NPDES permited sewage lagoon output.
The Little Waishkey Below is a 2nd order stream that is sampled below an NPDES permited sewage lagoon output.
Little Waishkey River at Lakeshore Dr. is a 2nd order stream and is sampled during winter and spring runoff as sites normally visited for this stream are unaccessible.
Monocle Lake is hydrologically connected to Spectacle Lake an important rice lake for the community.  Monocle Lake is also an important sport fishery for bass, perch, and walleye.
North Pond is a fen that has no houses on the shoreline, but a few houses near the pond.  The east end of the pond has a buffer of trees then Gumshoes RV Park and Campground.
Parish Creek 1 is a 2nd order stream and is sampled near the parking lot of the Bay Mills Casino and Resort.
Parish Creek 2 is a 2nd order stream and is sampled near a parking lot drainage system.
Parish Creek Above is a 2nd order stream and is sampled above the Wild Bluff Golf Course.
Parish Creek Below is a 2nd order stream and is sampled below the Wild Bluff Golf Course.
Pontys Creek is a first order stream and is sampled below the golf course and where there is sediment deposition from upstream erosion.
Pontys Creek is a first order stream and is sampled below the golf course and where there is sediment deposition from upstream erosion.
St. Mary's River is sampled offshore of a populated area with septic tanks.
St. Mary's River is sampled at the shoreline of a populated area with septic tanks.

Spectacle Lake has one unpopulated basin located on the Reservation where the sample is taken.  The other basin is not sampled and has a few houses.  The rest of the lakeshore is owned by the forest service.
South Pond is a stained pond bordered by a swamp on the west side and a road on the east.  South Pond is the most populated inland pond/lake on the reservation.
St. Mary's River is sampled above Sugar Island Lands in the middle of the shipping channel.   This site is located downstream from a bi-national Area of Concern.
Wetland 1 is part of the Bay Mills Wetland Preserve and is sampled in a slow flowing spring near an old dump site.
Wetland 2 is part of the Bay Mills Wetland Preserve and is sampled in a intermittently wet area that is used by recreational ORVs.
Wetland 3 is part of the Bay Mills Wetland Preserve and is sampled due to its convenient location and water level.  The water level in wetland 3 is the highest of the 3 wetland sites.
The Whitefish Bay Reserve is sampled in a deep area.
The Whitefish Bay Reserve is sampled close to shore in a sparsely populated area.
Boat docking area in need of shoreline restoration.
Boat docking area in need of shoreline restoration.
The Waishkey River is a 5th order stream that is the largest inlet to Back Bay.  The river and its tributaries run through mostly argricultural and forested land.
This site will give us information on the entire West Branch of the Waishkey River; sampled at Bound Road near WR11 and WR12.
This site will give us information on the entire South Branch of the Waishkey River; sampled at Bound Road near WR10 and 12.
Hutton Creek of the Waishkey River; sampled at Bound Road.  This branch of the WR receives inputs from the NPDES permitted Kinross Township WWTP.
Beaver Creek of the Waishkey River sampled at White Road.  This is the northeastern most branch of the WR that drains predominantly agricultural areas.
Waishkey River sampled just downstream of the confluence of Besseau Creek.  WR1a is also sampled directly downstream of the M28 road-crossing.
Waishkey River sampled just upstream of a tributary that may drain a private sewage lagoon.  Sampled just downstream of WR1a.
Waishkey River sampled directly downstream of WR1b and a tributary that may drain a private sewage lagoon.
Waishkey River Sampled directly upstream of confluence with Orrus Creek.
Waishkey River Sampled directly downstream of confluence with Orrus Creek.
East Branch of the Waishkey River sampled directly upstream to the confluence with the West Branch of the Waishkey River.
West Branch of the Waishkey River sampled directly upstream to the confluence with the East Branch of the Waishkey River.
This site replaces Site WR4, and is sampled at 7 1/2 mile Rd.
